---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Qibla Now | Offline prayer times and Qibla direction"
  description="Qibla Now is an offline-first Islamic utility for prayer times, Qibla direction, alarms, and map guidance with privacy-first design."
>
  <section class="hero section">
    <div class="hero-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Offline-first Islamic utility</p>
        <h1>Prayer times and Qibla direction, without noise.</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          Qibla Now is built for speed, clarity, and trust: accurate prayer times, precise Qibla
          direction, local alarms, and no accounts, no analytics, no telemetry.
        </p>

        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="button button-primary" href="/features">See features</a>
          <a class="button button-secondary" href="/privacy">Privacy first</a>
        </div>

        <ul class="hero-points">
          <li>Works offline after installation</li>
          <li>On-device prayer and Qibla calculation</li>
          <li>Minimal, distraction-free experience</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <aside class="hero-panel card">
        <img src="/screenshots/home.png" alt="Qibla Now home screen" class="hero-image" />
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="grid-3">
      <article class="card info-card">
        <h3>Prayer times</h3>
        <p>
          Accurate daily prayer schedules with configurable calculation methods, madhab selection,
          and high-latitude rules.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card info-card">
        <h3>Qibla direction</h3>
        <p>
          Great-circle bearing toward the Kaaba, shown through compass, map, and numeric direction.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card info-card">
        <h3>Privacy by design</h3>
        <p>
          No accounts, no analytics, no telemetry, no backend, and no personal data collection.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Why it is different</p>
        <h2>A tool, not a platform.</h2>
        <p>
          Qibla Now is designed as a religious utility first. It focuses on the few tasks that
          matter during prayer-related moments and avoids the clutter, tracking, and dependency
          patterns common in modern mobile apps.
        </p>
        <p>
          The product goal is simple: reliable information, fast interaction, and calm execution.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card value-card">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Offline-first:</strong> core functionality remains available without internet.</li>
          <li><strong>No cloud dependency:</strong> calculations happen locally on the device.</li>
          <li><strong>No tracking:</strong> no analytics, telemetry, or remote logging.</li>
          <li><strong>Minimal ads:</strong> banner-only, non-personalized, never on core prayer screens.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="card trust-card">
      <div class="grid-2 trust-grid">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Trust model</p>
          <h2>Designed to respect privacy and attention.</h2>
          <p>
            External network use is limited to optional integrations such as maps and ads. Core
            religious functionality does not depend on a project-owned backend.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="trust-points">
          <div>
            <strong>No accounts</strong>
            <p>No sign-up, no profile, no personal identity layer.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong>No telemetry</strong>
            <p>No analytics, no crash reporting, no hidden behavioral data pipeline.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong>Non-personalized ads only</strong>
            <p>Ads are limited and configured to avoid profiling and tracking.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <strong>Local settings and logic</strong>
            <p>Preferences and calculations remain device-side.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding-top: 3rem;
  }

  .hero-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: stretch;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    max-width: 46rem;
  }

  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .hero-points {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0;
    list-style: none;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .hero-points li {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.8rem;
  }

  .hero-panel {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #ffffff 0%, #fbfaf4 100%);
  }

  .hero-image {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 14px;
  }

  .hero-panel-inner {
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .panel-title {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--brand-dark);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .mini-list {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .info-card,
  .value-card {
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .value-card ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
  }

  .value-card li + li {
    margin-top: 0.8rem;
  }

  .trust-card {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #ffffff 0%, #f8f6ee 100%);
  }

  .trust-grid {
    align-items: start;
  }

  .trust-points {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .trust-points > div {
    padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 16px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
  }

  .trust-points p {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  @media (min-width: 900px) {
    .hero-grid {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.4fr) minmax(320px, 0.8fr);
    }
  }
</style>